Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

TO ALSO INCLUDE 22CF77, 10CM459, 10CT151, 19CM681 & 19TR4754 (PLEAS):
CO: RMW , REP: Melstrom, CLERK: Liddle ADA:   Erica Ellenwood   DF ATTY:  Jon Elton Stanek   DF:  Garrett Ross Raebel appeared from jail by video means. Case called at 11:50 a.m. Court notes these matters are scheduled for a plea and sentencing hearing. New complaint was filed 22CF77 with OWI 5th charge. On 22CF77, Court reviews right to a preliminary hearing. DE understands and waives preliminary hearing. Court finds DF has freely, voluntarily, and knowingly waived the right to a preliminary hearing, finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the DF probably committed that felony and binds over for trial. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads GUILTY to Ct 1 OWI 5th in 22CF77. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Reviews right to be present in person. DE understands and waives in person appearance. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights, right to personal appearance and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1 OWI 5th in 22CF77. On motion of the State without objection, Crt dismisses 10CM459, 10CT151, 19CM681 & 19TR4754. Sentencing arguments. 20 days to appeal. Court adjourned at 12:09 p.m. 

Crt orders:
In Ct. 1 OWI 5th in 22CF77:
- S/W 2 years probation. Run concurrent to 10CT54. 

- Complete all other programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the Department of Corrections

- Impose 180 day jail sentence. Run concurrent to jail sentence in 10CT54. Credit for good time. Huber for any purpose the jail allows. 60 days jail credit. 

- AODA and Drivers Safety Plan

- Minimum court costs. To be added to current payment plan

- 30 month drivers license revocation. Credit for any administrative suspension.
